174 // Function to initialize the logging system
175 void LogData_PID::logInitializeLogging()
176 {
177  // Get the current date and time
178  auto now = std::chrono::system_clock::now();
179  std::time_t now_c = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(now);
180 
181  // Get the current date in the desired format
182  std::stringstream date_ss;
183  date_ss << std::put_time(std::localtime(&now_c), "%Y%m%d"); // Current date
184  std::string current_date = date_ss.str();
185 
186  // Create the directory path for the logs
187  std::string log_base_directory = "./src/flightstack/log/" + current_date + "/" + ControlType::getControllerName();
188 
189  // Check if the directory exists, and create it if it doesn't
190  if (!std::filesystem::exists(log_base_directory)) {
191  std::filesystem::create_directories(log_base_directory);
192  }
193 
194  // Check if the "logs" subdirectory exists within the log_base_directory, create it if needed
195  std::string logs_directory = log_base_directory + "/logs";
196  if (!std::filesystem::exists(logs_directory)) {
197  std::filesystem::create_directories(logs_directory);
198  }
199 
200  // Check if the "gains" subdirectory exists within the log_base_directory, create it if needed
201  std::string gains_directory = log_base_directory + "/gains";
202  if (!std::filesystem::exists(gains_directory)) {
203  std::filesystem::create_directories(gains_directory);
204  }
205 
206  // Generate the log file name with a timestamp
207  std::stringstream log_ss;
208  log_ss << logs_directory << "/log_" << std::put_time(std::localtime(&now_c), "%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") << ".log";
209  std::string log_filename = log_ss.str();
210 
211  // Add the "Tag" attribute with a constant value of "LogDataTag" to the logger
212  LogData_PID::logger_logdata.add_attribute("Tag", attrs::constant<std::string>("LogDataTag"));
213 
214  // Define a synchronous sink with a text ostream backend
215  typedef sinks::synchronous_sink<sinks::text_ostream_backend> text_sink;
216  boost::shared_ptr<text_sink> logdata_sink = boost::make_shared<text_sink>();
217 
218  // Add a stream to the backend (in this case, a file stream)
219  logdata_sink->locked_backend()->add_stream(boost::make_shared<std::ofstream>(log_filename));
220 
221  // Set the formatter for the sink
222  logdata_sink->set_formatter(
223  expr::stream
224  << "[" << expr::format_date_time<boost::posix_time::ptime>("TimeStamp", "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f") << "] " // Format date and time
225  << "[" << expr::attr<boost::log::attributes::current_thread_id::value_type>("ThreadID") << "] " // Current thread ID
226  << "[" << expr::attr<std::string>("Tag") << "] " // Tag attribute value
227  << "[" << expr::attr<boost::log::attributes::current_process_id::value_type>("ProcessID") << "] " // Current process ID
228  << "[" << expr::attr<unsigned int>("LineID") << "] " // Line ID
229  << expr::smessage // Log message
230  );
231 
232  // Add the sink to the logging core
233  logging::core::get()->add_sink(logdata_sink);
234 
235  // Set a filter for the sink
236  logdata_sink->set_filter(expr::has_attr("Tag") && expr::attr<std::string>("Tag") == "LogDataTag");
237 
238  logging::add_common_attributes(); // Add attributes like timestamp
239 
240  // Copy the gains file to the gains_directory with a new name containing the time info
241  std::string source_file = "./src/flightstack/params/control/pid/gains_pid.json";
242  std::stringstream target_ss;
243  target_ss << gains_directory << "/gains_pid_" << std::put_time(std::localtime(&now_c), "%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") << ".json";
244  std::string target_file = target_ss.str();
245 
246  if (std::filesystem::exists(source_file)) {
247  std::cout << "GAINS FILE PRESENT" << std::endl;
248  std::filesystem::copy(source_file, target_file);
249  } else {
250  std::cout << "GAINS FILE NOT PRESENT" << std::endl;
251  }
252 
253  logInitializeHeaders();
254 }
